At a family level, our parents are among millions of other victims who lost their sources of income.Thousands of pupils in private schools are also Kenyans who need to enjoy the taxes paid by their parents. When our headteacher announced that we were breaking in March 2020 due to Covid-19, we never anticipated it would be for this long.
Now, even as schools reopen after almost a year-long break, some of us — like my sister and I — have no school to go to.
Our former school, Wheatfield Education Complex in Sobea, Nakuru County, could not endure the ravages of the coronavirus pandemic.



